The Town Crier learns if a Minion nominated today. In this case, the Artist (a Townsfolk), Vigormortis (a Demon) and Mutant (an Outsider) nominated today. None of those characters are Minions, so the Town Crier will learn a no.
Each night, the Oracle learns how many dead players are evil. In this case, there are two dead evil players - Will the Cerenovus and Lachlan the Pit-Hag.
Each day, the Savant may visit the Storyteller to learn two things: one is true, and one is false. In this case, it is true that there is a Vigormortis in play, and false that there is a Fang Gu in play.
Once per game, the Seamstress may choose two players and learn if they are the same alignment. In this case, Patrick has chosen the evil Fang Gu and the good Juggler, so will learn no - they are not the same alignment. Don’t steal Patrick’s wallet, as that is not covered by the rules, and is immoral.
Once per game, at night, the Philosopher may choose a good character and gain that character’s ability. As an unfortunate side effect, if that character is already in-play, they become drunk. In this case, the Philosopher chose the Artist, which makes Lachlan (the actual Artist) drunk.
Once per game, the Artist can ask the Storyteller a yes or no question. In this case, Jon is the Evil Twin, so the Artist will get a yes. Storytellers should not freak out on their players without good reason.
On their first day, the Juggler can publicly guess up to 5 players' characters. That night, they learn how many of those guesses were correct. In this case, 2/4 of the Juggler’s guesses were correct, so they will learn a 2.
When the Demon kills the Sage, the Sage learns the Demon is 1 of 2 players. In this case, the Sage would learn Steven and one other player.
If the Mutant is mad about being an Outsider, they might be executed. A Mutant publicly claiming that they are the Mutant counts as being mad as an Outsider. A Mutant execution will immediately end the day.
When the Sweetheart dies, another player is made drunk for the rest of the game. In this case, Patrick has been made drunk.
After the Barber dies, the Demon is given the opportunity to choose two players. Those two players swap characters. 
When the Klutz learns that they have died, they must publicly choose a player. If the player they choose is evil, the Klutz’s team immediately loses. In this case, they chose Amy the evil Vortox, so evil wins.
If the good twin is executed while the evil twin lives, the evil team wins.
Each night, the Witch chooses a player. If that player nominates tomorrow, they die on the spot. This does not end the day.
Each night, the Cerenovus chooses a player and a good character. That player learns that the Cerenovus has selected them, and the character they selected. If they are not mad as that character tomorrow, they might be executed, which immediately ends the day. In this case, Reggie did not pretend to be the Clockmaker, so might be executed.
At night, the Pit-Hag must choose a player and a character. If that character is not already in-play, the chosen player becomes that character. In this case, because there is no Mutant already in-play, Jams becomes the Mutant
The first time an Outsider would be killed by a Fang Gu, the Outsider becomes an evil Fang Gu instead, and the attacking Fang Gu dies. In this case, Jon is the first Outsider that a Fang Gu has attacked, so Jon becomes an evil Fang Gu instead.
In addition to poisoning a Townsfolk neighbour, Minions killed by the Vigormortis keep their ability. As such, despite being dead, Ben the Pit-Hag can keep using his ability as normal. He will not die in real life, because this is just a board game.
The No Dashii poisons its 2 Townsfolk neighbours. In this case, the closest Townsfolk on either side are Reggie the dead Flowergirl and Ben the alive Philosopher.
The Vortox ability means that all Townsfolk abilities give false information. Theo is the Demon, so you must tell the Artist false information.
The Vortox ability means that Townsfolk abilities must yield false information. However, the Dreamer ability also requires that the Dreamer must learn a good and an evil character. So in this case, the Dreamer must learn a good and an evil character, neither of which are actually Will’s character (meaning, the Sage cannot be one of the two characters the Dreamer learns).
Usually, a drunk Dreamer could learn true or false information. However, the Vortox ability means that Townsfolk abilities must yield only false information. This trumps drunkeness, so the Dreamer must learn 2 characters that Steffen is not.
The Vortox ability does not prevent the Snake Charmer ability from working.
If a Snake Charmer swaps characters & alignment with the Demon via its ability, the new Snake Charmer is poisoned. This means its ability does not work, and selecting the new Demon does nothing.
When a player becomes a character, they enter play as a ‘new’ version of that character. All abilities are refreshed. If a Snake Charmer (poisoned by their own ability) swaps with someone else, the new Snake Charmer will not be poisoned.
If the Snake Charmer chooses the Demon, the two players swap character & alignment. In this case, because both Chloe and Lachlan are evil, they remain evil and just swap characters.
The Town Crier learns if a Minion nominated today. While Will was the Pit-Hag, he nominated. The Town Crier ability tracks what happened during the day, so Jon will get a yes.
Due to the Vortox ability, the Savant must learn two statements that are false.
Once a Philosopher dies, their ability goes away. If they were making a good character drunk, they stop making that character drunk. In this case, Ben dying means that Lachlan the Artist is no longer drunk.
The Juggler ability is: ""On your 1st day, publicly guess up to 5 players' characters. That night, you learn how many you got correct."" ‘Your 1st day’ means the first day that the Juggler was in-play, not the first day of the game. So, Steffen will receive information.
The Evil Twin and the good twin know who each other are, and what each others’ characters are. On the first night, they wake up together.
Executing the good twin only loses the game for the good team while the Evil Twin is still alive. If the Evil Twin is already dead when the good twin is executed, nothing happens.
While both twins are alive, the good team cannot win. If the only living players are the two twins, the game ends and evil wins. For this reason, the good team must deal with the twins earlier in the game - a final 3 consisting of only the twins and the Demon is an automatic loss for the good team.
The No Dashii poisons its closest Townsfolk neighbours. If Reggie becomes the Witch (a Minion), the next-closest anticlockwise Townsfolk neighbour of the No Dashii (Ben the Sage) will become poisoned instead.
The Evil Twin always learns an opposing player & their character. If a good Evil Twin is created, they will wake up with & learn the character of an evil player.
If the good player in a twin pair is executed, evil wins. In this case, Reggie is the good player (the good Evil Twin). Therefore, Reggie being executed means that evil wins.
The Evil Twin must always be paired with an opposing player. If the good player the Evil Twin is paired up with turns evil, the Evil Twin gets paired up with a new good player. So in this case, Steffen and Amy stop being a twin pair, and Steffen gets paired up with someone else. 
Dead players like Edd may still be affected by the Cerenovus, and can still be executed for breaking madness. This can be quite useful - a dead player being executed ends the day and prevents the town from executing a living player that day. However, if the Cerenovus dies, the Cerenovus ability is no longer in play, so it cannot cause a player to be executed. The player that was affected by the Cerenovus that night is not told that the Cerenovus is dead, however. 
In this case, there is already a Sweetheart in-play. As such, Ben’s character will not change.
If a Pit-Hag turns a player into a Demon, deaths that night are arbitrary. This means they are decided by the Storyteller, and any number of players can die. If the Pit-Hag tries to create two living evil Demons, Storytellers will usually use the Pit-Hag ability to kill one of them.
Only one Outsider may be converted into an evil Fang Gu. After this has happened, subsequent Outsiders who are attacked by a Fang Gu die as normal.
When the Vigormortis kills a Minion, one of that Minion’s Townsfolk neighbours becomes poisoned. A Townsfolk neighbour is the closest Townsfolk on either side. In this case, Patrick’s Townsfolk neighbours are Steffen and Amy, so either could be poisoned.
When players change characters, any effects that their characters were previously causing end. The Vigormortis and Witch swapping characters means that effects that were generated by the old Vigormortis, such as the Pit-Hag retaining their ability after death, end.
The Vortox ability means that if there is ever a day where no one is executed, the evil team instantly wins.
Two players’ abilities functioned abnormally (since dawn) due to another character’s ability. The Klutz picked an evil player, but did not make the good team lose, because they were drunk. The Dreamer learned 2 false characters, due to the Vortox. The Snake Charmer ability didn’t trigger despite them picking the Demon, but this will not register to the Mathematician. This is because the Snake Charmer was poisoned due to their own ability, not the ability of another character. So the correct number is 2. However, due to the Vortox, the Mathematician must learn false information, so will learn any number but a 2.
The Washerwoman has seen the Empath and the Spy players. Because the Spy can register as a Townsfolk, the Washerwoman could learn any Townsfolk character.
Steven is the Drunk who thinks he is the Librarian. As such, you can show him any 2 players, and any Outsider.
The Recluse can register as a Minion. That means, in this case, the Investigator could learn that Jams or another player is the Scarlet Woman (or any Minion you choose).
The Recluse can register as evil. The Spy can register as good. Both are sitting next to the Imp. So the Chef can learn a 0 (if both Recluse & Spy register as good), a 1 (if one registers as evil), or a 2 (if both register as evil).
There is one good player who registers as the Demon to the Fortune Teller. In this case, that player is Edd, so the Fortune Teller will get a yes.
If an Imp kills themselves with their own ability, a Minion becomes the Imp.
When a Monk chooses someone, that player is safe from the Demon tonight. This includes preventing a Demon from dying to their own ability. A Minion only becomes the Imp if the Imp kills themselves with their own ability - so nothing happens.
Normally, the Recluse could register as the Recluse, any Minion, or the Imp, all of which you could show to Ben. In this case, however, the Recluse is poisoned, so you could only show Ben the Recluse.
If a Townsfolk nominates the Virgin, the Townsfolk player is executed. The Spy might register as a Townsfolk, so Steffen may or may not be executed.
The Recluse can register as the Demon, meaning they might die to the Slayer’s ability. This death is not an execution, and will not bring an end to the day.
If the Mayor dies at night, another player might die instead. In such a situation, the Imp’s attack would effectively be redirected. The only player that this cannot kill is Patrick. Patrick is the Soldier, and the Soldier is safe from the Demon.
If the Mayor dies at night, the Storyteller can decide that another player dies instead - redirecting the Imp’s attack. In this case, the Imp’s attack has been redirected to Patrick, who is the Soldier. Because the Soldier is safe from the Demon, no players will die to the Imp’s attack.
The Mayor’s ability can redirect the Imp’s own attack back at them. If the Imp dies to their own ability this way, a Minion becomes the Imp.
The Butler cannot vote unless their Master is voting. Sometimes, they may accidentally do so anyway. This is unfortunate, but in most cases, it is better to just let the vote be counted (and privately remind them later that they must follow the restrictions of their ability). Publicly altering the vote tally would confirm that Lachlan is the Butler, which would be excellent for the good team, and not a great outcome for game balance.
If the Drunk is poisoned, nothing changes for them. A poisoned Drunk functions exactly the same as a non-poisoned Drunk. They do not learn that they are the Drunk.
The Drunk thinks they are a Townsfolk, but they are actually the Drunk. Abilities that detect a player's character, such as the Undertaker, will learn that the Drunk is the Drunk, not that they are the character they think they are.
The character the Recluse is registering as can change. They could register as a Minion or Demons to one player’s ability, a different Minion or Demon  to another player, and then actually register as the Recluse to someone else.
When a player changes character, they do not retain the abilities of the character they were before. If Lachlan becomes the Imp, the Poisoner ability will no longer be in-play, and Steven will no longer be poisoned.
If there are 5 or more players alive when the Demon dies, the Scarlet Woman becomes the Demon. This still triggers if the Demon dies when there are exactly 5 players alive - the Scarlet Woman instantly becomes the Demon. Ben Dance is not in a coma, please do not suggest this to him.
The Imp must choose a player with their ability each night.
The Imp may target a dead player with their ability. If they do, no players will die to the Demon tonight.
